<br>
What I do is ask the MA and SA what their hitpoints are.  Then I use their hitpoints to decide when I should start healing.  I use a hotkey for each and this is what it looks like:<br>
<br>
The name of my MA hotkey is MA.<br>
/tar Beomur (This is the Main Assist)<br>
/pause 3<br>
/cast 8 (This is where my healing spell gem is located)<br>
<br>
The name of my SA hotkey is SA.<br>
/tar Kerawin (This is the Second Assist)<br>
/pause 3<br>
/cast 8<br>
<br>
I watch my other healers mana status.  When the main healers for their groups are Low On Mana (LOM), I tell them I am backing up their heals on the MA and SA.  When I am LOM, another healer from another group backs up my heals on the MA and SA.<br>
<br>
There is usually a chain-heal line that is set up by the raidleader or the main raid healer.<br>
<br>
Unless the beastie is using a lot of AE damage spells, the meelee's in my group usually do not need much healing....just alot of hugs and moral support. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I hope this helps a bit.<br>
<br>
